In c language storage classes are defined as

    where a variable is stored in memory
    scope of the variable
    life of the variable

Types of storage classes:
    There are 4 Types of storage classes
        1.auto
        2.register
        3.static
        4.extern

refer with the usage and examples of all above storage classes 
and then compare with below table

Storage Class	    Scope	            Lifetime	        Default Value	    Stored in
   auto	        Local (function)	Till function ends	    Garbage value	     Stack
 register	    Local (function)	Till function ends	    Garbage value	    CPU Register
  static	      Local/Global	    Entire program run	           0	        Data Segment
  extern	    Global (all files)	Entire program run	           0	        Data Segment